cent <i>-s</i>."]}]},{"name":"Frances","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Feminine form of   Francis .  In the 16th century the two spellings were used indiscriminately for both sexes, the distinction in spelling not being established until the 17th century."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":45,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Frances Powell was born in 1410, in Sussex, England. She had at least 1 son with Thomas Grantham Alford. She died in 1460, in England, at the age of 50."},"et":{"1410–1460":"1410–1460","1405–1440":"1405–1440","1430–1487":"1430–1487","1455":"1455","1410":"1410","1487":"1487","1430":"1430","1440":"1440","1460":"1460","1405":"1405","England":"England","Sussex, England":"Sussex, England","Whitestaunton, Chard, Somerset, England":"Whitestaunton, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1410–1460":"1410–1460","1405–1440":"1405–1440","1430–1487":"1430–1487","1455":"1455","1410":"1410","1487":"1487","1430":"1430","1440":"1440","1460":"1460","1405":"1405","England":"England","Sussex, England":"Sussex, England","Whitestaunton, Chard, Somerset, England":"Whitestaunton, Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1410–1460":"1410–1460","1405–1440":"1405–1440","1430–1487":"1430–1487","1455":"1455","1410":"1410","1487":"1487","1430":"1430","1440":"1440","1460":"1460","1405":"1405","England":"Angleterre","Sussex, England":"Sussex, Angleterre","Whitestaunton, 